revision.text:
'''Dennis L Hartmann''' is an American atmospheric scientist at the [[University of Washington]].  He has done research on [[ozone depletion]] and [[climate change]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atmos.washington.edu/~dennis/|title=Professor D. L. Hartmann|publisher=Atmos.washington.edu|accessdate=9 November 2014}}</ref>

In 2016 he was elected to the [[National Academy of Sciences]].<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.nasonline.org/news-and-multimedia/news/may-3-2016-NAS-Election.html|title=National Academy of Sciences Members and Foreign Associates Elected|department=News from the National Academy of Sciences|publisher=[[National Academy of Sciences]]|date=May 3, 2016|accessdate=2016-05-14}}.</ref>
He is a [[Roger Revelle Medal|Revelle Medal]] committee member.<ref>https://sites.agu.org/leadership/committees/council-committees/medal-selection-committees/revelle-medal-committee/</ref>

