{{Infobox protected area | name = Dunajské trstiny | iucn_category = III | photo = | photo_caption = | area = 1.041016 km²<ref name="official">[http://uzemia.enviroportal.sk/main/detail/cislo/1120 ''Štátny zoznam osobitne chránených častí prírody SR''] {{sk icon}}</ref> | established = 2002 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = ŠOP - S-CHKO Dunajské luhy |external_link = }}
'''Dunajské trstiny''' is a nature reserve in the [[Slovakia|Slovak]] municipalities of [[Veľké Kosihy]] and [[Klížska Nemá]] in the [[Komárno District]]. The nature reserve covers an area of 104.1016&nbsp;ha of the Danube floodplain area. It has a protection level of 4 under the Slovak nature protection system.<ref name="official" />
==Description== The area protects continuous reed communities. It presents a possibility to study the final stage of the silting process, houses wetland and hydrophile plant species and presents nesting places for wetland and reed birds.<ref name="official" />
