This is a listing of minor planets orbiting the Sun by their approximate distance from the [[Sun]] in March 2018 (as opposed to those with the greatest calculated [[aphelion]] in their orbit). In March 2018 several new [[Trans-Neptunian object]]s (TNOs) with a current heliocentric distance greater than 50 AU were announced by [[Scott S. Sheppard]], [[Chad Trujillo]], and [[David J. Tholen]].<ref>[https://twitter.com/astrokiwi/status/973329908297543681 MPECs 2018-E75 to E78 and MPECs 2018-E83 to E90. Planetary astronomer Michele Bannister]</ref>
Trans-Neptunian objects are typically announced publicly months or years after their discovery, so as to make sure the orbit is correct before announcing it. Due to their greater distance from the Sun and slow movement across the sky, trans-Neptunian objects with [[observation arc]]s less than several years often have poorly constrained orbits. Particularly distant asteroids discovered in 2018 may only be announced in 2020 or later.
